preview_comments.text: Beautiful shot bro. I would love that walk to work everyday. Amazing views. Looking forward to Modern Warfare very soon👍🏻😊

Love the vibe of your photos. 💯 I'm counting the days till the release of Death Stranding. The fact that this game is coming out is still miraculous to me. I mean, starting from zero again, building up a new studio from the ground up with no staff, with no tech, and making a triple-a game full of new and unique ideas, all in less than four years? That's not something anyone can do. This game is actually Kojima trying to prove everyone (most definitely his former employer) not only he's still in the game, but that he's even more influential and bigger than before.

caption.text:
An oldie, but I think a goodie. Gotta love walks along the Yarra before work. Now sadly winter is gone however mild mornings are amazing. Of course taking my controller for a walk haha.

As Falling In Reverse put it so nicely in the tune Game Over “my life is like a video game, trying hard to beat the stage, all while I am still collecting points”

So question time, what game are you looking forward to?

The Lure of the Loot Box for Gamers With Gambling Tendencies 🕹️⠀
.⠀
Gamers who are drawn to “loot boxes”—randomly generated prizes of undisclosed value that can be attained or purchased within a game—bear a closer resemblance to problem gamblers than they do to problem gamers, according to the study published April 16 in Addictive Behaviors.⠀
.⠀
When the researchers analyzed the scores, they found a correlation between excessive engagement with loot boxes and measures of problem gambling, supporting the view that loot boxes are a ‘gamblified’ feature of modern video games. They found a smaller correlation between loot boxes and problem video gaming.⠀
.⠀
📝 https://doi.org/10.1016/j.addbeh.2019.04.009⠀
.⠀

caption.text:
Excited to add The Walking Dead: the TellTale definitive series game which collects all four seasons, 400 days, and the Walking Dead Michonne episodes to the collection, but bummed that the full contents of the Guardian Pack from @Skybound games has been delayed until later this year.

I got an email regarding the delay stating that the Clementine and Lee diorama statue was the source of some quality issues out of the factory so the delay was to increase that production value with a follow up release.

Once I get the full collectors edition in hand, I’ll be doing a follow up post with all the goodies that come with it.

Oh and with October right around the corner you’ll start to see Halloween decorations start showing up in my setup...well hello Oogie Boogie and Jack!
